text.section:
Service of process is sufficient service on a nonresident driver if:
Service is made by the personal delivery and leaving of a copy of the process, with a certification of the last known address of the nonresident driver, with the Motor Vehicle Administration;
A fee for service of process is paid to the Motor Vehicle Administration;
The Motor Vehicle Administration sends a copy of the process by certified mail, return receipt requested, to the nonresident driver at the nonresident driver's last known address; and
The Motor Vehicle Administration files an affidavit of compliance with the provisions of this section with the clerk of the court in which the action is pending.

The Motor Vehicle Administration shall report to the General Assembly on or before January 1 of each year, in accordance with § 2-1246 of the State Government Article, the following information for the preceding calendar year:
The total number of subpoenas, summonses, and other service of process issued in accordance with the provisions of this section;
The number of instances in which the Motor Vehicle Administration failed to reach the individual being served and the reasons that those attempts failed;
A breakdown of all direct and indirect costs incurred by the Motor Vehicle Administration in carrying out the requirements of this section; and
The total fees collected by the Motor Vehicle Administration from persons requesting service of process under this section.
